Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Finely chop half the @rosemary{1/4%ounce}(chopped) (all for 4 servings).

Toss carrots on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Toss potatoes on empty side of baking sheet with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{}, rosemary, a pinch of @salt{}, and pepper.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a second baking sheet. Wipe out pan.

> Swap in pork or beef for chicken. Cook pork until browned and cooked through, 4-8 minutes, or cook beef to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side.

Roast on middle rack until chicken is cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}. Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

Meanwhile, roughly chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}.

Once veggies and chicken are done roasting, combine @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}, @water{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings), and @pepper{} in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat.

Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer and cook, whisking constantly, until slightly reduced, ~{30-60%seconds}. TIP: If sauce is too thick, add water 1 tsp at a time until sauce reaches desired consistency.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken, potatoes, and carrots between plates in separate sections. Spoon sauce over chicken and potatoes and sprinkle with parsley. Serve.

> Slice chicken or beef against the grain.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.